INSERT INTO `committee` VALUES (1,13,'Administrative and Finance Committee (AFC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>An Administrative and Finance Committee oversees and manages a variety of administrative and financial issues, playing an important function inside organisations. The organization\'s financial stability, compliance, and strategic planning are all impacted by its duties, which also include budgeting, financial reporting, policy formulation, audit monitoring, risk management, and more. The committee\'s membership and powers may change based on the structure and objectives of the organisation, but its main tasks are to guarantee solid financial management, openness, and efficient governance.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The specific responsibilities and objectives associated with an Administrative and Finance Committee:</p><ul><li><strong>Budgeting:</strong> The committee is usually responsible for developing and reviewing the organization\'s budget, which includes revenue projections, expense allocations, and financial planning.</li><li><strong>Financial Reporting:</strong> It oversees financial reporting processes, ensuring that financial statements, reports, and records are accurate and in compliance with relevant accounting standards and regulations.</li><li><strong>Financial Policies:</strong> Developing and recommending financial policies and procedures to ensure sound financial management and compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>Specific functions and activities of the committee:</p><ul><li><strong>Audit Oversight:</strong> Coordinating and overseeing external audits, internal audits, or financial reviews to assess the organization\'s financial health and internal controls.</li><li><strong>Investment Decisions:</strong> Making recommendations on investment strategies, managing reserves, and overseeing the organization\'s investment portfolio.</li><li><strong>Risk Management:</strong> Assessing and managing financial risks, including insurance coverage, and ensuring the organization has appropriate risk management strategies in place.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Ensuring compliance with tax laws, financial regulations, and legal requirements, including filing necessary reports and documentation.</li><li><strong>Asset Management:</strong> Managing and safeguarding the organization\'s assets, such as property, equipment, and investments.</li><li><strong>Contract Review:</strong> Reviewing and approving contracts, vendor agreements, and financial agreements to ensure they align with the organization\'s financial goals.</li><li><strong>Strategic Planning:</strong> Contributing to the development of the organization\'s financial and administrative strategic plans and goals.</li><li><strong>Governance:</strong> Collaborating with the board of directors or governing body to ensure transparency, accountability, and good governance practices.</li><li><strong>Reporting to Leadership:</strong> Regularly reporting financial updates, recommendations, and findings to the organization\'s leadership or board of directors.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Administrative and Finance Committee (AFC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Jatin Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Principal)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit Dholakiya</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Maulik Pandya</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Information technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Nirav Bhavsar</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Viral Patel</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Hitesh Patel</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Biochemistry and Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Chirag vyas</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Rupesh Jha</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>','undefined','2023-10-19',NULL),(9,13,'Internal Quality Assurance Cell (IQAC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>IQAC stands for the Internal Quality Assurance Cell, and it is a vital component within educational institutions, primarily in higher education. The role and responsibilities of an IQAC are to enhance and ensure the quality and effectiveness of education, teaching, research, and overall institutional performance.</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Internal Quality Assurance Cell (IQAC) is to ensure and enhance the quality of education and overall institutional performance in higher education institutions. The IQAC aims to establish a system for continuous improvement in all aspects of the institution\'s functioning, including academic, administrative, and governance, by:</p><ul><li><strong>Assessing and monitoring the quality of teaching, learning, and research:</strong> The IQAC evaluates the effectiveness of academic programs, teaching methodologies, and research activities to ensure they meet predefined quality standards.</li><li><strong>Fostering a culture of quality consciousness:</strong> It works to instil a culture of continuous improvement, accountability, and transparency among all stakeholders, including faculty, staff, and students.</li><li><strong>Promoting research and innovation:</strong> The IQAC encourages and supports research and innovation activities within the institution to advance knowledge and contribute to academic excellence.</li><li><strong>Enhancing student outcomes:</strong> It focuses on improving the academic performance, employability, and overall development of students through various initiatives and feedback mechanisms.</li><li><strong>Ensuring compliance with accreditation and regulatory requirements:&nbsp;</strong>The IQAC ensures that the institution complies with accreditation standards, statutory regulations, and other quality-related guidelines.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>The functions of an IQAC are wide-ranging and involve various activities and processes aimed at continuous quality enhancement. Some of the key functions typically include:</p><ul><li><strong>Development and Implementation of Quality Policies:</strong> Formulating and implementing policies and procedures related to quality assurance and enhancement in line with the institution\'s mission and vision.</li><li><strong>Quality Assurance Framework:&nbsp;</strong>Developing a quality assurance framework that includes quality benchmarks, key performance indicators (KPIs), and assessment criteria for various academic and administrative activities.</li><li><strong>Academic Program Review:</strong> Conducting periodic reviews of academic programs to assess their relevance, curriculum quality, and alignment with learning outcomes.</li><li><strong>Feedback and Surveys:</strong> Collecting feedback from students, faculty, and other stakeholders through surveys, focus groups, and feedback mechanisms to identify areas for improvement.</li><li><strong>Faculty Development:</strong> Organizing workshops, seminars, and training programs for faculty members to enhance their teaching and research skills.</li><li><strong>Research Promotion:</strong> Encouraging and supporting research activities among faculty and students, including facilitating research grants and collaborations.</li><li><strong>Student Support Services:</strong> Ensuring the availability of support services such as counselling, career guidance, and academic advising to enhance the student experience.</li><li><strong>Infrastructure and Resource Management:</strong> Monitoring and ensuring the availability of necessary infrastructure, facilities, and resources for academic and research activities.</li><li><strong>Accreditation and Quality Audits:</strong> Preparing the institution for accreditation processes, self-assessment, and external quality audits.</li><li><strong>Data Collection and Analysis:</strong> Collecting and analysing data related to academic performance, research output, and other relevant parameters to inform decision-making.</li><li><strong>Documentation and Reporting:</strong> Maintaining records, reports, and documentation related to quality assurance activities and outcomes.</li><li><strong>Continuous Improvement:</strong> Identifying areas for improvement based on data and feedback, and implementing corrective and preventive actions.</li><li><strong>Stakeholder Engagement:</strong> Engaging with stakeholders, including alumni, industry partners, and employers, to gather input and feedback on the institution\'s quality and relevance.</li><li><strong>Benchmarking:</strong> Comparing the institution\'s performance and practices with benchmark institutions to identify best practices and areas for improvement.</li><li><strong>Ethical Practices:</strong> Ensuring ethical practices in research, teaching, and administration, including addressing issues related to plagiarism and academic integrity.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>IQAC Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr Jatin D Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Chairman, Principal of SANPPGIS&amp;R</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Vishant Patel</td><td>Co-Ordinator, Department of Chemistry</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Sameer Patel</td><td>Member, Representative of Management</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Parimal Chavda</td><td>Member, Principal, D. N. Institute of Business Administration, Anand</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Naynesh Purohit</td><td>Member, I/C Principal, Shri I. J. Patel B.Ed. College, Mogri</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Mitesh Patel</td><td>Member, Administrative office</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Darshan Patel</td><td>Alumni</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jayesh Gosai</td><td>Alumni Parents</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>IQAC</strong></p><p><strong>Meeting Minutes:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>2018-19</strong></td><td><a href=\"https://api.cesociety.in/pdf/1699077981332.pdf\"><strong>View Document</strong></a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>2019-20</strong></td><td><a href=\"https://api.cesociety.in/pdf/1699078058104.pdf\"><strong>View Document</strong></a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>2021-22</strong></td><td><a href=\"https://api.cesociety.in/pdf/1699078109035.pdf\"><strong>View Document</strong></a></td></tr><tr><td><strong>2022-23</strong></td><td><a href=\"https://api.cesociety.in/pdf/1699078162724.pdf\"><strong>View Document</strong></a></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>','null','2023-10-19','2023-11-04'),(11,13,'Academic Planning and Development Cell (APDC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>An Academic Planning and Development Cell (APDC) is a specialized unit or committee within an educational institution, typically in higher education, responsible for coordinating and overseeing various aspects of academic planning, curriculum development, and faculty development.</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><p>The Academic Planning and Development Cell (APDC) in educational institutions typically has the following key objectives:</p><ul><li><strong>Academic Excellence:</strong> To strive for and enhance academic excellence by developing and implementing strategies that improve the quality of teaching, learning, and research within the institution.</li><li><strong>Curriculum Development:</strong> To design, review, and update academic programs and curricula to ensure they remain current, relevant, and aligned with industry standards and educational goals.</li><li><strong>Faculty Development:</strong> To support the professional development of faculty members by offering training, workshops, and opportunities for research and skill enhancement.</li><li><strong>Resource Allocation:</strong> To efficiently allocate resources, including faculty, infrastructure, and funding, to different academic departments and programs based on academic priorities.</li><li><strong>Student-Centric Approach:</strong> To focus on student-centric initiatives, including student support services, mentoring, and fostering an environment conducive to holistic student development.</li><li><strong>Accreditation and Quality Assurance:</strong> To work towards achieving and maintaining accreditation from relevant accrediting bodies and to ensure adherence to quality assurance standards.</li><li><strong>Academic Planning:</strong> To engage in long-term and short-term academic planning to align the institution\'s academic goals with its broader mission and vision.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Academic Planning and Development Cell may vary depending on the institution\'s specific needs and goals. However, common functions often include:</p><ul><li><strong>Curriculum Development:</strong> Collaborating with academic departments to design and revise curricula that meet the latest educational standards, industry demands, and student needs.</li><li><strong>Program Review:</strong> conducting periodic reviews of academic programs to assess their effectiveness, relevance, and alignment with the institution\'s objectives.</li><li><strong>Faculty Development:</strong> Organizing faculty development programs, workshops, and training sessions to enhance teaching methodologies, research capabilities, and professional skills</li><li><strong>Resource Management:</strong> Allocating resources such as faculty positions, research funds, laboratories, and infrastructure to different academic departments based on academic priorities</li><li><strong>Quality Assurance:</strong> Implementing quality assurance measures to ensure the quality and integrity of academic programs and research activities</li><li><strong>Student Support Services:</strong> Offering student support services such as academic advising, counseling, career guidance, and mentorship to facilitate student success</li><li><strong>Academic Policies:</strong> formulating and updating academic policies and regulations, including grading systems, academic integrity codes, and admission criteria.</li><li><strong>Accreditation Preparation:</strong> Preparing the institution for accreditation processes by ensuring that all academic programs and activities meet the required standards</li><li><strong>Data Analysis:</strong> Collecting and analyzing data related to academic performance, enrollment trends, student outcomes, and faculty productivity to inform decision-making.</li><li><strong>Strategic Planning:</strong> Contributing to the development and implementation of the institution\'s strategic plan, with a focus on academic goals and priorities</li><li><strong>Research Promotion:</strong> encouraging and supporting research activities by providing grants, resources, and incentives for faculty and students.</li><li><strong>Innovation and Technology Integration:</strong> Promoting the integration of innovative teaching methods and technology to enhance the learning experience</li><li><strong>Outcome Assessment:</strong> Implementing assessment methods to measure learning outcomes and using the results for continuous improvement</li><li><strong>Budgeting:</strong> Collaborating with the finance department to allocate budgets for academic initiatives and ensure efficient resource utilization</li><li><strong>Feedback Mechanisms:</strong> Establishing mechanisms for collecting feedback from students, faculty, and other stakeholders to assess the effectiveness of academic programs and services</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Collaborating with other institutional units, academic departments, and external partners to advance academic goals and initiatives</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Academic Planning and Development Cell (APDC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Chirag U Vyas</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator</strong> (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit Mangrola</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Viral Surati</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit Dholakia</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Anjali Mahida</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Maitri P. Pokar</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Kailash Tiwari</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>Academic and Administrative Audit</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Academic and Administrative Audit Policy&nbsp;</td><td><a href=\"https://api.cesociety.in/pdf/1699078510400.pdf\">View Document&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></td></tr><tr><td><p>Academic and Administrative Audit</p><p>2023-24</p></td><td><a href=\"https://api.cesociety.in/pdf/1699078928075.pdf\">View Document</a></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','undefined','2023-10-19','2023-11-04'),(12,13,'Institutional Exam Committee (IEC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>An Institutional Exam Committee (IEC) is a committee or administrative body established within educational institutions to oversee and manage various aspects of the examination process. Its role is critical in ensuring the fairness, integrity, and efficiency of examinations conducted by the institution. The IEC operates under a framework of rules and regulations established by the institution and relevant educational authorities.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an institutional exam committee is to ensure the effective planning, administration, and evaluation of examinations within the institution. It strives to create an environment conducive to a fair and transparent assessment of students\' knowledge and skills. The IEC\'s overarching goals include:</p><ul><li><strong>Fairness:</strong> To ensure that examination processes are fair to all students, free from bias, and uphold academic integrity.</li><li><strong>Quality Assurance:</strong> To maintain the quality and standards of examinations, aligning them with the institution\'s educational objectives.</li><li><strong>Transparency:</strong> To promote transparency in examination procedures, from question paper setting to result publication.</li><li><strong>Efficiency:</strong> To manage examination logistics efficiently, reducing administrative errors and disruptions during exams.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> To ensure compliance with regulatory requirements, accreditation standards, and institutional policies related to examinations.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions of the Committee:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Institutional Exam Committee encompass a wide range of responsibilities related to the planning, execution, and post-examination phases of assessment. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Exam Schedule:</strong> Creating and publishing exam schedules, including dates, times, and venues for various examinations</li><li><strong>Question Paper Setting:</strong> Ensuring the secure and unbiased setting of examination question papers and adherence to quality standards</li><li><strong>Invigilation and Security:</strong> Managing the recruitment and training of invigilators and implementing security measures to prevent cheating or malpractice during exams</li><li><strong>Logistics and Infrastructure:</strong> Coordinating facilities, resources, and logistics required for smooth conduct of examinations</li><li><strong>Special Accommodations:</strong> Addressing the needs of students with disabilities and arranging for appropriate accommodations during exams</li><li><strong>Conflict Resolution:</strong> Handling disputes, grievances, and irregularities related to examinations, including the investigation of academic misconduct.</li><li><strong>Result Processing:</strong> Overseeing the timely and accurate processing of examination results, including grading and score compilation.</li><li><strong>Data Security:</strong> Ensuring the security and confidentiality of examination data and records</li><li><strong>Feedback and Improvement:</strong> Collecting feedback from students and faculty regarding the examination process and implementing improvements based on feedback</li><li><strong>Compliance and Reporting:</strong> Ensuring compliance with regulations, preparing reports for accreditation bodies, and facilitating external audits or reviews.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Institutional Exam Committee (IEC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Hitesh Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Biochemistry)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Vishant C. Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Viral Surati</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Hetal Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Abhishek B Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Mahendra Dabhi</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Sneha Dodiya</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-10-19',NULL),(13,13,'Extra-Curricular Activities Committee (ECAC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Extra-Curricular Activities Committee (ECAC) is a vital component within educational institutions and other organizations, responsible for overseeing and facilitating a wide range of activities and events that complement the formal academic curriculum. These activities, often referred to as co-curricular or extra-curricular activities, include sports, clubs, cultural events, and various other non-academic pursuits. The ECAC\'s role is to organize, manage, and support these activities to enrich the educational experience and personal development of participants.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Extra-Curricular Activities Committee is to enhance the overall development of individuals within the institution by providing opportunities for participation in diverse activities beyond the classroom. The key objectives typically include:</p><ul><li><strong>Holistic Development:</strong> To promote the holistic development of students or participants by offering a range of activities that nurture their physical, social, emotional, and intellectual growth.</li><li><strong>Talent Exploration:</strong> To provide a platform for individuals to explore and develop their talents, interests, and passions outside of the academic curriculum.</li><li><strong>Community Building:</strong> To foster a sense of community and belonging among students, staff, and other stakeholders through shared interests and activities.</li><li><strong>Leadership and Soft Skills:</strong> To develop leadership, teamwork, communication, and problem-solving skills through participation in clubs, teams, and organizations.</li><li><strong>Health and Wellness:</strong> To encourage physical fitness and well-being by promoting sports and recreational activities.</li><li><strong>Cultural Awareness:</strong> To celebrate diversity and promote cultural awareness by organizing cultural festivals, events, and exhibitions.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions of the Committee:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Extra-Curricular Activities Committee encompass a wide range of responsibilities related to the planning, organization, and management of co-curricular and extra-curricular activities. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Activity Planning:</strong> Identifying, planning, and scheduling a variety of activities, clubs, and events that cater to the interests and talents of participants</li><li><strong>Resource Allocation:</strong> Managing budgets and resources to support the activities, including funding, venues, equipment, and materials.</li><li><strong>Student Engagement:</strong> encouraging and facilitating student participation in clubs, teams, and events through recruitment, registration, and promotion.</li><li><strong>Advisor and Mentorship:</strong> Appointing advisors or mentors for clubs and teams to provide guidance and support to participants</li><li><strong>Event Coordination:</strong> organizing and overseeing events, competitions, workshops, and exhibitions</li><li><strong>Safety and Compliance:</strong> Ensuring the safety and well-being of participants during activities and compliance with relevant policies and regulations</li><li><strong>Recognition and Awards:</strong> Recognizing and rewarding outstanding achievements and contributions in co-curricular and extra-curricular activities</li><li><strong>Feedback and Improvement:</strong> Gathering feedback from participants and stakeholders to improve the quality and relevance of activities</li><li><strong>Public Relations:</strong> Promoting the achievements and activities of the institution\'s co-curricular and extra-curricular programs to the broader community.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Extra Co-curricular Activities Committee (EAC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Darshan Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Chemistry)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Dipeksha Macwan &nbsp;</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Janki Trivedi</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Rutvik Prajapati</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Rinkal Mulani</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Maitri P Pokar</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Megha H Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Jinal Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Lab. Technology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-10-19',NULL),(14,13,'Career Guidance, Counseling, Training and Placement Cell (CTPC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Career Guidance, Counseling, Training, and Placement Cell (CTPC) serves as a bridge between educational institutions and the corporate world. It plays a pivotal role in enhancing students\' employability and ensuring they secure suitable job opportunities.</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Career Guidance:</strong> Provide career counseling and guidance to students, helping them make informed decisions about their career paths.</li><li><strong>Employability Enhancement:</strong> Organize training programs, workshops, and seminars to improve students\' soft skills, technical skills, and overall employability.</li><li><strong>Industry Interaction:</strong> Foster strong ties with industries and companies to facilitate internships, projects, and campus placements for students.</li><li><strong>Placement Assistance:</strong> Assist students in finding suitable job opportunities by arranging campus placement drives and connecting them with potential employers.</li><li><strong>Alumni Network:</strong> Maintain an alumni network to leverage the experiences and connections of former students to aid current students\' career development.</li><li><strong>Feedback Mechanism:</strong> Gather feedback from recruiters and students to continuously improve the quality of education and training programs.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Career Counseling:</strong> Provide one-on-one counseling to students to help them identify their strengths, weaknesses, and career goals.</li><li><strong>Training Programs:</strong> Conduct workshops and training sessions on resume writing, interview preparation, communication skills, and personality development.</li><li><strong>Industry Collaborations:</strong> Establish partnerships with companies and industries to facilitate internships, industrial visits, and guest lectures.</li><li><strong>Placement Drives:</strong> Organize campus placement drives where companies visit the campus to recruit students.</li><li><strong>Resume Building:</strong> Assist students in creating effective resumes and cover letters tailored to specific job applications.</li><li><strong>Mock Interviews:</strong> Conduct mock interviews to prepare students for real job interviews and provide constructive feedback.</li><li><strong>Job Notifications:</strong> Keep students informed about job openings, internships, and career-related events.</li><li><strong>Data Management:</strong> Maintain a database of student profiles, placements, and recruiter information.</li><li><strong>Feedback and Assessment:</strong> Collect feedback from recruiters and students to evaluate the effectiveness of the placement process and training programs.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Career Guidance, Counselling, Training and Placement Cell (CTPC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Nirav Bhavsar</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Microbiology)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Jaimin R Avalani</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit Mangrola</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Jitendria Panigrahi</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Sarita Shah</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Viral patel</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ankur J Khimani</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-10-19',NULL),(15,13,'Sports Committee','<p><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>An Institutional Sports Committee (ISC) is a governing body or committee typically established within educational institutions, businesses, or organizations to oversee and promote sports and athletic activities. The primary focus of the ISC is to facilitate the development of sports programs, organize sports events and competitions, and support the physical well-being and recreational needs of students, employees, or members.</p><p><strong>Objectives:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Institutional Sports Committee is to promote physical fitness, sportsmanship, teamwork, and a healthy lifestyle among its constituents. The key objectives often include:</p><ul><li><strong>Sports Development:</strong> To foster the development of sports and athletic talent among students, employees, or members.</li><li><strong>Physical Fitness:</strong> To encourage physical fitness and well-being by providing opportunities for regular exercise and sports participation.</li><li><strong>Competition and Excellence:</strong> To organize sports events and competitions that promote healthy competition and excellence in sports.</li><li><strong>Recreation:</strong> To provide recreational opportunities for individuals to relax, unwind, and de-stress through sports and physical activities.</li><li><strong>Sports Culture:</strong> To instill a culture of sportsmanship, fair play, and teamwork among participants.</li><li><strong>Talent Identification:</strong> To identify and nurture talented athletes and provide them with opportunities for further training and competition.</li></ul><p><strong>Function:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The functions of an Institutional Sports Committee encompass a wide range of responsibilities related to sports program development, event organization, facilities management, and promotion of physical fitness. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Sports Program Planning:</strong> Developing an annual or long-term sports program that includes a variety of sports and activities catering to different interests and skill levels.</li><li><strong>Event Organization:</strong> Organizing sports events, tournaments, and competitions within the institution, including inter-school or inter-college events.</li><li><strong>Facilities Management:</strong> Managing sports facilities such as playing fields, courts, gyms, and equipment to ensure their proper maintenance and availability.</li><li><strong>Coaching and Training:</strong> Providing coaching and training opportunities for athletes and teams to enhance their skills and performance.</li><li><strong>Intramural and Extramural Sports:</strong> Organizing intramural sports leagues and extramural sports participation, where teams or individuals represent the institution externally.</li><li><strong>Equipment and Uniforms:</strong> Procuring and maintaining sports equipment and uniforms for teams and participants.</li><li><strong>Safety and Health:</strong> Ensuring the safety and health of participants during sports activities by implementing safety protocols and providing medical support when needed.</li><li><strong>Promotion and Marketing:</strong> Promoting sports events and programs through marketing and communication channels to attract participants and spectators.</li><li><strong>Records and Statistics:</strong> Maintaining records of sports achievements, statistics, and participant data for analysis and recognition.</li><li><strong>Awards and Recognition:</strong> Recognizing outstanding athletes and teams through awards, certificates, and honours.</li><li><strong>Budget Management:</strong> Managing the budget allocated for sports programs, events, and equipment.</li><li><strong>Gender Inclusivity:</strong> Promoting gender inclusivity in sports by providing equal opportunities and support for both male and female participants.</li><li><strong>Feedback and Evaluation:</strong> Gathering feedback from participants and stakeholders to assess the quality and effectiveness of sports programs and events.</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Collaborating with other institutional units, external sports organizations, and authorities to enhance sports programs and facilities.</li><li><strong>Community Engagement:</strong> Involving the broader community and alumni in sports activities and events, fostering a sense of belonging and support.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Sport Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mr. Mitesh Damor</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Chemistry)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Dhruv Kapadi</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Hiral Chaudhari</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Narendra Patil</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Nidhi Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Megha Vyas</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Mahendra Dabhi</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ankurkumar Khimani</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-10-19','2023-12-06'),(17,13,'Anti-Ragging Cell','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>An Anti-Ragging Cell&nbsp;is a specialized committee or administrative body established within educational institutions, particularly in colleges and universities, to prevent and address incidents of ragging. Ragging refers to any form of physical, mental, or emotional harassment or abuse inflicted upon new students by seniors or peers, often as a harmful tradition or initiation ritual.</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Anti-Ragging Cell is to create a safe and welcoming environment within the educational institution for all students, free from the fear of ragging or any form of harassment. The key objectives typically include:</p><ul><li><strong>Prevention:</strong> To prevent incidents of ragging and hazing through awareness, education, and strict enforcement of anti-ragging policies.</li><li><strong>Safety:</strong> To ensure the safety and well-being of new students and protect them from any form of physical or psychological harm.</li><li><strong>Deterrence:</strong> To deter seniors or perpetrators from engaging in ragging activities by imposing stringent penalties for violations.</li><li><strong>Support:</strong> To provide support and counseling to victims of ragging and assist them in overcoming the trauma and stress associated with such incidents.</li><li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> To ensure compliance with anti-ragging laws, regulations, and directives issued by relevant authorities.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Anti-Ragging Cell are crucial in creating and maintaining a ragging-free environment within the institution. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Awareness Campaigns:</strong> Conducting awareness campaigns and orientation programs for new students to educate them about the consequences of ragging and the importance of reporting incidents.</li><li><strong>Complaint Registration:</strong> Establishing channels for students to report incidents of ragging confidentially and ensuring that complaints are addressed promptly.</li><li><strong>Investigation:</strong> Investigating reported incidents to determine the facts, identify the perpetrators, and collect evidence for appropriate action.</li><li><strong>Disciplinary Actions:</strong> Imposing disciplinary actions, which may include suspension or expulsion, against students found guilty of engaging in ragging.</li><li><strong>Counseling Services:</strong> Providing counseling and support services to victims and assisting them in coping with the emotional and psychological impact of ragging.</li><li><strong>Student Orientation:</strong> Including anti-ragging awareness as an integral part of student orientation programs and induction processes.</li><li><strong>Monitoring and Reporting:</strong> Regularly monitoring the institution\'s premises and student activities to identify and prevent any ragging-related incidents.</li><li><strong>Liaison with Authorities:</strong> Collaborating with local law enforcement and educational authorities to ensure the enforcement of anti-ragging laws and regulations.</li><li><strong>Legal Support:</strong> Assisting victims in seeking legal action against perpetrators when necessary and cooperating with legal authorities during investigations.</li><li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Maintaining records of reported incidents, actions taken, and outcomes for future reference and compliance reporting.</li><li><strong>Annual Reports:</strong> Preparing and submitting annual reports on the status of ragging within the institution to relevant authorities.</li><li><strong>Orientation of Staff:</strong> Sensitizing faculty, staff, and security personnel to the prevention and reporting of ragging incidents.</li><li><strong>Support for Whistleblowers:</strong> Ensuring protection and support for students or individuals who come forward as witnesses or whistleblowers in ragging cases.</li><li><strong>Conflict Resolution:</strong> Promoting a culture of conflict resolution and non-violence among students.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Anti-Ragging Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Chirag U. Vyas</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Physics)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Zarna Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Viral Surati</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Siddhi Shah</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Meghaben Vyas</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms Dipeksha Macwan</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Viral Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Kailash Tiwari</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Shobha Verma</td><td>Member (Department of Information Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jaimin Zala</td><td>Member student (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','undefined','2023-12-06',NULL),(18,13,'Alumni Association Cell (AAC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Alumni Association Committee plays a pivotal role in fostering a strong and enduring connection between a school, college, or institution and its former students. This committee is instrumental in maintaining and nurturing the alumni network, which can be a valuable asset for the institution in various ways. The Alumni Association Committee serves as a bridge between the institution and its alumni, facilitating engagement, networking, and support.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of the Alumni Association Committee is to create a vibrant and mutually beneficial relationship between the institution and its alumni. This relationship is built upon several key objectives:</p><ul><li><strong>Engagement and Networking:</strong> The committee aims to facilitate meaningful engagement and networking opportunities among alumni. This involves organizing reunions, alumni gatherings, and events that encourage alumni to connect with each other and with the institution.</li><li><strong>Support for Institutional Growth:</strong> Alumni often have a deep affinity for their alma mater and are willing to contribute to its growth. The committee\'s objective includes soliciting support from alumni in the form of donations, mentorship programs, and expertise sharing to benefit the institution.</li><li><strong>Career Development:</strong> The committee strives to assist alumni in their professional development by organizing career workshops, job fairs, and mentorship programs that leverage the expertise and experience of successful alumni.</li><li><strong>Preservation of Institutional Heritage:</strong> Alumni often hold a wealth of institutional history and traditions. The committee seeks to preserve and document this heritage for current and future generations by collecting and archiving alumni stories and memorabilia.</li><li><strong>Promotion of Alumni Achievements:</strong> Celebrating the accomplishments of alumni is an essential objective. The committee highlights and promotes the achievements of alumni in various fields, showcasing their successes as a source of inspiration for current students.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>The Alumni Association Committee carries out its objectives through a range of functions and activities, including:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Event Organization:</strong> Planning and executing alumni events, such as reunions, homecoming celebrations, and networking receptions, to encourage alumni to reconnect with each other and the institution.</li><li><strong>Fundraising and Development:</strong> Initiating and managing fundraising campaigns, scholarships, and alumni giving programs to secure financial support for the institution\'s growth and development.</li><li><strong>Communication:</strong> Maintaining regular communication with alumni through newsletters, social media, and alumni websites to keep them informed about institutional developments and upcoming events.</li><li><strong>Career Services:</strong> Providing career support to alumni through job placement assistance, resume workshops, and networking opportunities.</li><li><strong>Database Management:</strong> Maintaining an up-to-date database of alumni contact information and tracking their achievements and contributions.</li><li><strong>Heritage Preservation:</strong> Collecting and archiving historical documents, photographs, and memorabilia to preserve the institution\'s heritage.</li><li><strong>Alumni Recognition:</strong> Organizing awards and recognition programs to honour outstanding alumni and their contributions to society.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Alumni Association Cell (AAC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mr. Viral Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Mathematics)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Yati Vaidya</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Priyal Soni</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit&nbsp; &nbsp;Mangrola</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Sarita Shah</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ankur J Khimani</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Kailash Tiwari</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(19,13,'Women Protection and Development Cell (WPDC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>Collegiate Women Development Cell (CWDC) was constituted in Shri Alpesh N. Patel Post Graduate institute of Science and Research, Anand with the initiative to raise and resolve the problems faced by girl students and women staff of the college. The issues related to violence against women have paralyzed our society for years. Women Development Cell is a platform to unite the youth who can ignite a wave of change in the society. The objective of the Women Development Cell is to create awareness among the girls and the women staff, apart from maintaining congenial working environment for all the women employees and students.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>&nbsp;Objectives:</strong></p><ul><li>To prevent sexual harassment and to promote the general well-being of female students, teaching and non-teaching women staff of the college.</li><li>To organize various types of training programmes and self-employment schemes for the encouragement of self-reliance among women.</li><li>In case of sexual harassment in the premises of the college, active assistance shall be provided to the complainant by the cell to pursue the complaint and the safety of the complainant shall be ensured.</li></ul><p><strong>Penalties and Punishment for Sexual Harassment</strong></p><p>The committee shall impose the following penalties on a person found guilty of sexual harassment:</p><p>A student found guilty of sexual harassment shall be liable to following penalties:</p><ul><li>Warning</li><li>Written apology</li><li>Suspension for a specified period of time</li></ul><p><strong>Instruction to the Students</strong></p><ul><li>Proper dress code should be followed. Body fit clothing, transparent or revealing outfits should be avoided.</li><li>Girl students should refrain from using shortcuts to reach their places.</li><li>Sharing of mobile phone numbers with the unknown persons should be avoided.</li><li>Sexual harassment involves unwelcome words, deeds, symbols actions, gestures that make the woman uncomfortable.</li><li>Sexual assault or sexual harassment or sexual misconduct is an offence and viable for criminal proceedings.</li></ul><p><strong>Steps towards Safety of Female Students &amp; Employees</strong></p><ul><li>Surveillance cameras are installed at various places of the college to monitor and safeguard the safety of students and employees of the college.</li><li>Security guards are instated in the college campus to restrict the entry of any person other than student or employee of the college.</li><li>Identity cards of the students are checked by the guards at the entrance.</li></ul><p><strong>Working&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>A meeting of all the members of the CWDC is convened on a regular basis in which issue related to women safety and security are discussed.</li><li>The programme related to women empowerment, health and awareness are chalked out by the members of the cell.</li><li>A facility of vending machine and disposal machine for girl students of the college.</li></ul><p><strong>Programmes Conducted by Collegiate Women Development Cell (CWDC)</strong></p><ul><li>Lectures on Gender Education were conducted.</li><li>Lectures on Women’s rights and laws to help.</li><li>Programmes concerning Gender sensitization were arranged.</li><li>Expert Lectures related to the issues of PCOD and health hygienic were organized.</li><li>Yoga training session was organized.</li><li>Lecture on create awareness against ragging and women laws was organized.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Committee members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Women Protection and Development Cell (WPDC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Dr. Zarna Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Chemistry)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Megha H Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Nidhi Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Sneha Dodia</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Hetal Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Dipali K. Chauhan</td><td>Member (Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Hardika Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Information Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Yati Vaidya&nbsp;</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Miss Prachi Panchal</td><td>Member student (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(20,13,'Institutional Purchase Committee (IPC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Institutional Purchase Committee (IPC) is a significant component in educational institutions, responsible for managing and overseeing the procurement of goods and services required by the organization to ensure efficient and cost-effective operations. The IPC plays a critical role in ensuring transparency, fairness, and compliance with procurement regulations and policies.</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Institutional Purchase Committee is to streamline the procurement process, optimize resource utilization, and ensure that the organization acquires goods and services of the required quality at the best possible cost. The key objectives often include:</p><ul><li><strong>Cost Efficiency:</strong> To procure goods and services at competitive prices to minimize expenditure and achieve cost savings for the organization.</li><li><strong>Transparency:</strong> To maintain transparency and accountability in procurement processes, ensuring that decisions are made in a fair and ethical manner.</li><li><strong>Quality Assurance:</strong> To ensure that the goods and services procured meet the organization\'s quality and performance standards.</li><li><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> To adhere to relevant laws, regulations, and internal policies governing procurement, including sustainability and diversity considerations.</li><li><strong>Risk Mitigation:</strong> To identify and mitigate procurement-related risks, such as supply chain disruptions or vendor non-compliance.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Institutional Purchase Committee encompass a wide range of responsibilities related to procurement, vendor selection, contract management, and compliance. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Needs Assessment:</strong> Identifying and prioritizing the organization\'s procurement needs based on departmental requirements and operational objectives.</li><li><strong>Vendor Evaluation:</strong> Evaluating and selecting vendors or suppliers through a competitive bidding process, taking into account factors such as price, quality, reputation, and compliance.</li><li><strong>Tendering and RFPs:</strong> Preparing and issuing tender documents, requests for proposals (RFPs), and other procurement-related documents.</li><li><strong>Bid Evaluation:</strong> Reviewing and assessing vendor bids, proposals, and quotations to determine the most suitable supplier.</li><li><strong>Negotiation:</strong> Negotiating terms and conditions of contracts with selected vendors, including pricing, delivery schedules, and performance expectations.</li><li><strong>Contract Management:</strong> Overseeing the execution of contracts, monitoring vendor performance, and ensuring compliance with contractual obligations.</li><li><strong>Budget Management:</strong> Managing and allocating budgets for procurement activities, including tracking and reporting expenditures.</li><li><strong>Record Keeping:</strong> Maintaining accurate records of procurement transactions, vendor agreements, and related documentation.</li><li><strong>Compliance and Reporting:</strong> Ensuring compliance with procurement regulations and reporting procurement activities to relevant authorities or oversight bodies.</li><li><strong>Sustainability Initiatives:</strong> Promoting environmentally sustainable procurement practices and considering eco-friendly options when feasible.</li><li><strong>Conflict Resolution:</strong> Resolving disputes or issues that may arise during the procurement process or contract execution.</li><li><strong>Vendor Relationship Management:</strong> Cultivating and managing relationships with vendors to foster positive, long-term partnerships.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Institutional Purchase Committee (IPC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Amit B. Dholakia</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Chemistry)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Vishal Soni</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Aksha Parekh</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry</td></tr><tr><td>­­Mrs. Bhakti H Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Mansi Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Priyanka Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jayesh Gosai</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Dhrasti Thakar</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Krupali Bavisa</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06','2023-12-06'),(21,13,'Web Maintenance and Media Cell (WMMC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Web Maintenance Committee of college works for functionality enhancement of the College website. The Committee takes strategic initiatives for the website in presenting it to the college authority for review for subsequent updation and addition. The Committee looks after the website design and user interface, and develops contents for timely update. The Committee systematically coordinates with other committees while updating and uploading relevant information.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Online Visibility:</strong> Enhancing the organization\'s visibility and accessibility on the internet to reach a wider audience, including clients, customers, students, or the general public.</li><li><strong>Information Dissemination:</strong> Facilitating the dissemination of accurate and timely information, news, updates, and announcements (University exams, University Academic calendar, University rank list etc., Global events like chandrayan-3, Luna-25, other astronomical events and Science news, etc.,) through website and digital channels.</li><li><strong>Brand Promotion:</strong> Promoting and maintaining the organization\'s brand identity, image, and reputation in the digital space.</li><li><strong>User Experience:</strong> Ensuring a positive user experience by creating user-friendly websites and interfaces that are accessible on various devices.</li><li><strong>Media Management:</strong> Managing and showcasing digital media assets, including images, videos, infographics, and other multimedia content.</li><li><strong>Engagement:</strong> Facilitating engagement and interaction with stakeholders, including website visitors, social media followers, and online communities.</li></ul><p><strong>Function:</strong></p><p>The functions of a Web Maintenance and Media Cell encompass a wide range of responsibilities related to digital content management, online communication, and media development. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Website Maintenance:</strong> Regularly updating and maintaining the organization\'s website to ensure it reflects current information, news, events, and services.</li><li><strong>Content Creation:</strong> Generating and curating engaging and informative content, including articles, blog posts, videos, and social media posts.</li><li><strong>Social Media Management:</strong> Managing and monitoring the organization\'s social media profiles, including content posting, engagement with followers, and reputation management.</li><li><strong>Multimedia Production:</strong> Creating and managing multimedia assets, such as videos, images, infographics, and interactive content.</li><li><strong>Search Engine Optimization (SEO):</strong> Optimizing digital content and websites for search engines to improve online visibility and discoverability.</li><li><strong>Analytics and Reporting:</strong> Tracking website and social media performance through analytics tools and generating reports to assess digital engagement and effectiveness.</li><li><strong>Digital Marketing:</strong> Planning and executing digital marketing campaigns, including email marketing, pay-per-click advertising, and social media advertising.</li><li><strong>Crisis Communication:</strong> Developing strategies for handling online crises or negative feedback effectively.</li><li><strong>Compliance and Security:</strong> Ensuring compliance with data protection and privacy regulations and maintaining the security of digital assets.</li><li><strong>User Training:</strong> Providing training and support to staff or users responsible for managing and updating digital content.</li><li><strong>Feedback and Improvement:</strong> Gathering feedback from users and stakeholders to make continuous improvements to the organization\'s digital presence.</li><li><strong>Online Reputation Management:</strong> Monitoring online mentions and reviews to maintain a positive online reputation.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Web Maintenance and Media Cell (WMMC)</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Mrs. Hardika Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Information Technology)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ashish Bhatt</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Simaran Punjabi</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit&nbsp; Mangrola</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ankit J. Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Abhishek Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Anjali&nbsp; Mahida</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Naredra Patil</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(22,13,'Institutional Marketing Cell','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Marketing Cell of an institute is a specialized team or department responsible for promoting and enhancing the institution\'s brand, attracting prospective students, and managing various marketing activities. Its primary focus is on increasing the institute\'s visibility, reputation, and enrolment through strategic marketing efforts.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The main objective of the Marketing Cell in an institute is to achieve the following:</p><ul><li><strong>Brand Promotion:</strong> Build and strengthen the institute\'s brand identity and reputation in the education sector.</li><li><strong>Student Recruitment:</strong> Attract a diverse pool of prospective students and convert them into enrolled students.</li><li><strong>Outreach:</strong> Expand the institute\'s reach to a wider audience, including potential students, parents, alumni, and industry partners.</li><li><strong>Communication:</strong> Effectively communicate the institute\'s offerings, values, achievements, and updates to various stakeholders.</li><li><strong>Engagement:</strong> Engage with the community, including current students, alumni, and faculty, to foster a sense of belonging and support.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><p>The Marketing Cell carries out several functions to achieve its objectives:</p><ul><li><strong>Market Research:</strong> Conduct market research to understand trends, competition, and the preferences of prospective students.</li><li><strong>Advertising and Promotion:</strong> Create and manage advertising campaigns across various channels, such as social media, print media, and online platforms.</li><li><strong>Digital Marketing:</strong> Utilize digital channels, including websites, email marketing, SEO, and social media, to reach a wider audience.</li><li><strong>Content Creation:</strong> Develop engaging content, such as blogs, videos, and infographics, to showcase the institute\'s strengths and offerings.</li><li><strong>Events and Outreach:</strong> Organize events, webinars, and workshops to engage with potential students and their parents.</li><li><strong>Public Relations:</strong> Build relationships with media outlets and manage public relations to generate positive coverage for the institute.</li><li><strong>Alumni Engagement:</strong> Foster strong connections with alumni to leverage their successes in marketing efforts.</li><li><strong>Data Analysis:</strong> Analyze data and metrics to measure the effectiveness of marketing campaigns and make data-driven decisions.</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Work closely with academic departments and administrative teams to align marketing strategies with the institute\'s goals.</li><li><strong>Budget Management:</strong> Allocate and manage budgets for marketing activities efficiently.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Institutional Marketing Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Nirav Bhavsar</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Microbiology)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mrs. Hardika Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Information Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit&nbsp; Mangrola</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr Kartik Mistry</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Abhishek Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Anjali Mahida</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Simaran Punjabi</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Jitendria Panigrahi</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(23,13,'Collage Development and Maintenance Cell','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The College Development and Maintenance Cell (CDMC) is a primary group of our institute which helps in planning activities related to the infrastructure and allied development in the college premise. This Cell is responsible for suggesting renovation of existing infrastructure also along with the planning of specific details related to students’ and faculties’ needs. CDMC acts as a body where students centric developments initiatives are proposed to the administration and management. CDMC also helps in formulation of those policies which improve the overall learning experience students can have from our institute.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The main objectives of CDMC are to draft a holistic plan for the development of the institute which can be executed every academic year. The job of this Cell is to propose to higher management, the initiatives related to academic and pedagogical improvements, creation of new infrastructure and their maintenance. CDMC also works towards improving placement and further studies prospects of the students. The planning for better execution of duties of administrative staff is also bestowed to CDMC which comprise the continual support to the newly admitted and pass-out students.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><ul><li>Creation of a professional plan for the development of institute in terms of academic growth, administrative efficiencies, pro-student initiatives, infrastructure improvement and a pleasant learning experience of students.</li><li>Creation of extracurricular activities modules for holistic growth of students.</li><li>Preparing an annual itinerary of teaching schedule and allied activities.</li><li>Proposing to higher authorities changes that are deemed necessary for various subjects.</li><li>Keeping tract of adequate teaching staff availability and filling administrative and back-office posts.&nbsp;</li><li>To enhance the research and scientific acumen of both teacher and students, raising requests to higher-ups for collaboration with premier institutes in and outside the country and with reputed corporate groups.&nbsp;</li><li>Creating a portfolio of requests to be raised to management for promotion and maintenance of ICT tools that can enable effective pedagogical.&nbsp;</li><li>Encouraging teaching and other staff to regularly update their knowledge and skills by undergoing professional training and attending seminars/workshops etc.&nbsp;</li><li>Preparation of estimation of annual budget for catering to financial needs of the institute’s seamless operation and growth.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Provisioning a contingency financial need in case a new and legitimate demand for the same arises during the course of running the institute in the said academic year. The contingency fund will be over and above the prepared annual budget.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Keeping employees aware with various welfare schemes promoted by state or central governments and requesting management of the institute to promote employee benefits.</li><li>&nbsp;To have constructive discussion with all stakeholder regarding the recommendations form IQAC team.</li><li>&nbsp;A seamless and quick process for admission of new students by making a joint effort through Sardar Patel University.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;To prepare the schedule and allocate suitable time and resources for conducting sports events, cultural programmes and annual day functions. Important national festivals and social events organization at suitable times.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;As per the guidelines laid out by various government and other agencies, make students aware about discipline and keeping sanctity of an educational organization. Also, raising awareness among students and staffs about legal action in case of ragging or any other type of harassment.&nbsp;</li><li>A professional report preparation regarding local audit committee’s visit and recommendation. To take measures for improving the ranking of the institute as the criterions of various regulatory bodies like National Assessment and Accreditation Council, National Institutional Ranking Framework etc.&nbsp;</li><li>To award the student achievers of that year with suitable scholarship and medals. To award the teaching and other staff in case of extraordinary achievements.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Before the end of academic calendar, drafting of an annual report about the initiatives planned and executed by CDMC and discuss the outcomes of planned goals.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Committee Members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Collage Development and Maintenance Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Rupesh Jha</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Biotechnology)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Vishal Soni</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Aksha Parekh</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry</td></tr><tr><td>­­Mrs. Bhakti H Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Mansi Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Priyanka Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Arunbhai Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Dhrasti Thakar</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Krupali Bavisa</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(24,13,'Library committee','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The Library Committee is comprised of experienced members of the Staff who have sound academic knowledge. They keep a track of the activities of the library and also have a record of the books and journals available in the library. The Committee upgrades the library based on the requirements of the Staff and the Students.</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><ul><li>Facilitating communication with and obtaining feedback from the Collage community on library collections, programs, services, infrastructure, and communication mechanisms.</li><li>To provide a forum for discussing collage library and its community’s needs and expectations for information.</li><li>To act as advocates for the library in collage ‐wide decision‐making groups.</li><li>To advise the library on policy matters concerning services, resources and facilities.</li><li>To provide an opportunity to raise and discuss initiatives in the provision of library and information services.</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><ul><li>Advises and reviews library policies for instruction, resources, services, and the facility</li><li>Discuss and evaluate budgetary issues for books, journals, databases, media, e-resources etc.</li><li>Reviews benchmarking reports with peer institutions for resources, staffing, and services</li><li>Ensures the library is connected with and supports the Collage academic programs.</li><li>Represent the views of the library’s stakeholders on library and information services</li><li>Deliberate and advise on the direction and development of policies for library and information services to ensure the best possible support is provided.</li><li>Support the Library’s efforts in ensuring financial accountability and responsibility in the provision of library collections.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Library committee</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Mr. Ankit Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Library)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Pritesh Thakor</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Chaitali Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ns. Nidhi Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jayesh Gosai</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Jinal Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Jitendria panigrahi</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jay Pandya</td><td>Member student (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06','2023-12-06'),(25,13,'Student’s welfare committee','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>The student’s welfare committee anticipates a supportive learning environment that is focused on the needs of the students as well as caring interactions between students and teachers. The Committee places an emphasis on the students\' overall development by attending to their needs, offering assistance to slow learners, and encouraging positive psycho-personal motivation and direction for them.&nbsp; The committee helps students to expand the horizons of their personality via a multitude of activities and events, including cultural festivals, technology meets, and other student development bodies.</p><p><strong>Objectives</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Student’s welfare</strong>: Committee act as an interface between students and administration, taking suggestions of students through drop box facility in college and on college website.</li><li><strong>At college level</strong>:&nbsp;<ul><li>To organize special meetings with the parents of those students whose fail to attend classes and show low performance in the class.</li><li>Committee develop strong student-teacher relationship bond by implementation of mentor- mentee programme and help the&nbsp;students with psychological issues to achieve reconciliation with the self and others (consulting college counselors)</li><li>Co-ordination with staff council committee for welfare of students</li><li>To organize programmes to make students job ready, strengthen the placement cell and make them aware of existing placement cells activities, motivate students to register.</li></ul></li><li><strong>At student level</strong>:<ul><li>Supply awareness about various plans, schemes, courses and programmes started for the development of students (such as internal complaints committee and medical facilities)</li><li>Inspire students to involve in Personality Development Classes in the college.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Hygiene condition</strong>:<ul><li>Maintain general hygiene in the campus</li><li>Building maintenance and hygiene</li><li>Monitor hygienic condition of canteen, food and drinking water&nbsp;</li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>Function:</strong></p><p>The functions of a Student\'s Welfare Committee encompass a wide range of responsibilities aimed at providing comprehensive support and services to students. These functions may include:</p><p><strong>Counseling and Guidance:</strong> Offering counseling services to help students address academic, personal, and emotional challenges, and providing career guidance.</p><p><strong>Financial Aid:</strong> Administering financial aid programs, scholarships, and grants to assist students with their educational expenses.</p><p><strong>Health Services:</strong> Facilitating access to healthcare services, including medical check-ups, vaccinations, and mental health support.</p><p><strong>Diversity and Inclusion:</strong> Promoting diversity and inclusion within the student community and addressing issues related to discrimination or harassment.</p><p><strong>Student Housing:</strong> Managing student housing facilities and addressing accommodation-related concerns.</p><p><strong>Career Services:</strong> Providing resources and assistance for job placements, internships, and career development.</p><p><strong>Student Activities:&nbsp;</strong>Organizing and supporting extracurricular activities, clubs, and student organizations that enrich the student experience.</p><p><strong>Safety and Security:</strong> Ensuring campus safety through the implementation of safety protocols, emergency response plans, and security measures.</p><p><strong>Health and Wellness Programs:</strong> Organizing wellness programs, fitness activities, and health awareness campaigns.</p><p><strong>Orientation and Transition Programs:</strong> Conducting orientation programs for new students and assisting with their smooth transition into the institution.</p><p><strong>Dispute Resolution:</strong> Resolving conflicts and disputes among students or between students and the institution.</p><p><strong>Feedback Mechanisms:</strong> Establishing channels for students to provide feedback and suggestions regarding their academic experience and support services.</p><p><strong>Student Advocacy:&nbsp;</strong>Advocating for students\' rights and interests within the institution and addressing their concerns at administrative levels.</p><p><strong>Financial Literacy:</strong> Offering workshops and resources to help students develop financial literacy skills.</p><p><strong>Community Outreach:</strong> Engaging with the broader community to create partnerships and opportunities for student engagement and service-learning.</p><p><strong>Committee Members</strong>:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Student’s welfare committee</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Amit Mangrola</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Biochemistry)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Mehul Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Rutvik Prajapati</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Dipeksha Macwan</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jayesh Gosai</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Ms. Jinal Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Jitendria panigrahi</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Kanaiya Gadhvi</td><td>Member student (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(26,13,'Hostel and Canteen committee','<p><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>A Hostel Management Committee&nbsp;is a committee or administrative body responsible for the effective operation and management of hostels or dormitories within educational institutions, residential facilities, or other organizations. Its primary role is to create a safe, comfortable, and conducive living environment for residents and to oversee various aspects of hostel management.</p><p><strong>Objective:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The primary objective of a Hostel Management Committee is to ensure the well-being and satisfaction of hostel residents by providing a secure, clean, and supportive living environment. The key objectives typically include:</p><ul><li><strong>Resident Welfare:</strong> To promote the physical, mental, and emotional well-being of hostel residents by addressing their needs and concerns.</li><li><strong>Safety and Security:</strong> To establish and maintain safety and security protocols to protect residents and their belongings.</li><li><strong>Infrastructure Maintenance:</strong> To ensure the proper maintenance of hostel buildings, facilities, and utilities.</li><li><strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> To comply with local regulations, codes, and standards governing hostel operations.</li><li><strong>Community Building:</strong> To facilitate a sense of community and mutual respect among hostel residents.</li></ul><p><strong>Function:&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The functions of a Hostel Management Committee encompass a wide range of responsibilities related to the day-to-day operations and long-term planning of hostels. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Admission and Allocation:</strong> Managing the admission process for new residents, including room allocation and roommate assignments.</li><li><strong>Infrastructure Maintenance:</strong> Overseeing the maintenance, repair, and renovation of hostel buildings and facilities, including plumbing, electrical systems, and common areas.</li><li><strong>Security and Surveillance:</strong> Implementing security measures, such as access control systems, CCTV cameras, and security personnel, to ensure the safety of residents.</li><li><strong>Rules and Regulations:</strong> Establishing and enforcing rules and regulations governing hostel conduct, including curfew hours, guest policies, and noise restrictions.</li><li><strong>Emergency Response:</strong> Developing and practicing emergency response procedures for incidents such as fires, medical emergencies, or natural disasters.</li><li><strong>Amenities and Services:</strong> Providing essential amenities and services to residents, such as laundry facilities, Wi-Fi access, dining services, and recreational areas.</li><li><strong>Complaint Resolution:</strong> Addressing resident complaints, concerns, and conflicts in a fair and timely manner.</li><li><strong>Health and Hygiene:</strong> Ensuring cleanliness and hygiene within the hostel premises, including regular cleaning and sanitation measures.</li><li><strong>Financial Management:</strong> Managing the budget and financial resources allocated for hostel operations, including collecting fees and allocating funds for maintenance and improvements.</li><li><strong>Resident Engagement:</strong> Organizing and promoting social, cultural, and recreational activities to foster a sense of community among residents.</li><li><strong>Health and Safety Training:</strong> Providing residents with information and training on health and safety practices and emergency procedures.</li><li><strong>Regular Inspections:</strong> Conducting regular inspections to assess the condition of the hostel and address any maintenance or safety issues.</li><li><strong>Feedback and Improvement:</strong> Gathering feedback from residents to make improvements in hostel management and services.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Hostel and Canteen committee</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Miss. Jinal Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Medical Technology)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Mitesh Damor</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ashish Bhatt</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Miss. Megha Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Physics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Jitendria Panigrahi</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Rahul Panpaniya</td><td>Member Student (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Miss Kruti Moradiya</td><td>Member Student (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','null','2023-12-06','2023-12-06'),(27,13,'Grievances Redressal Cell','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>An Institutional Grievances Redressal Cell (IGRC) is an administrative unit or committee established within educational institutions, government agencies, businesses, or other organizations to address and resolve grievances and complaints raised by stakeholders, including students, employees, customers, or the general public. The IGRC serves as a dedicated mechanism for handling grievances in a fair, impartial, and efficient manner.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Institutional Grievances Redressal Cell is to provide a structured and responsive platform for individuals to seek resolution for their grievances, concerns, or complaints related to the institution\'s policies, practices, or actions. The key objectives typically include:</p><ul><li><strong>Fairness and Justice:</strong> To ensure that grievances are addressed in a fair, unbiased, and transparent manner, upholding principles of natural justice.</li><li><strong>Conflict Resolution:</strong> To facilitate the resolution of disputes and conflicts through dialogue, negotiation, or mediation, thus preventing escalation.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> To ensure that the institution complies with applicable laws, regulations, and ethical standards in addressing grievances.</li><li><strong>Continuous Improvement:</strong> To gather feedback from grievances and use it to identify areas for improvement in institutional policies and practices.</li><li><strong>Stakeholder Satisfaction:</strong> To enhance the satisfaction and trust of stakeholders by demonstrating the institution\'s commitment to addressing their concerns.</li></ul><p><strong>Function:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Institutional Grievances Redressal Cell involve a systematic and structured approach to receiving, investigating, and resolving grievances. These functions may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Grievance Reception:</strong> Receiving and documenting grievances from stakeholders through various channels, such as email, forms, or in-person meetings.</li><li><strong>Evaluation:</strong> Assessing the validity and seriousness of grievances to determine whether they fall within the purview of the IGRC.</li><li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> Ensuring the confidentiality of the grievance process to protect the privacy and interests of both the complainant and the institution.</li><li><strong>Investigation:</strong> Conducting impartial investigations into grievances, including gathering evidence, interviewing relevant parties, and reviewing relevant documents.</li><li><strong>Mediation and Conciliation:</strong> Attempting to resolve grievances through mediation, conciliation, or negotiation when appropriate and agreed upon by the parties involved.</li><li><strong>Recommendations:</strong> Making recommendations for resolving grievances, which may include changes to policies, actions, or compensation.</li><li><strong>Communication:</strong> Providing clear and timely communication to the complainant about the status of their grievance and the resolution process.</li><li><strong>Appeals:</strong> Offering appeals process for complainants who are not satisfied with the initial resolution, ensuring that multiple levels of review are available.</li><li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Maintaining records of grievances, investigations, and resolutions for reference and reporting purposes.</li><li><strong>Reporting:</strong> Preparing regular reports on the status of grievances, their resolution, and any trends or systemic issues identified.</li><li><strong>Training:</strong> Providing training and awareness programs to stakeholders on the grievance redressal process and their rights.</li><li><strong>Policy Review:</strong> Periodically reviewing and updating institutional policies and procedures based on feedback and trends in grievances.</li><li><strong>Compliance Monitoring:</strong> Ensuring that the institution complies with legal and regulatory requirements related to grievances and complaints.</li></ul><p><strong>Committee members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Grievances Redressal Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Jatin Patel</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Principal)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit Dholakia</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Maulik Pandya</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Information technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Nirav Bhavsar</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Viral Patel</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Mathematics)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Hitesh Patel</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Biochemistry and Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Chirag vyas</td><td>Member (Head of the Department of Physics)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06','2023-12-06'),(28,13,'Entrepreneurship Development Programming (EDP) Cell','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>An Entrepreneurship Development Programming (EDP) Cell&nbsp;is a specialized unit or committee within educational institutions, government agencies, business incubators, or other organizations that is dedicated to fostering and promoting entrepreneurship and entrepreneurial skills among individuals. The EDP Cell serves as a platform for nurturing entrepreneurial talent, providing resources, guidance, and support to aspiring and budding entrepreneurs.</p><p><strong>Objective:</strong></p><p>The primary objective of an Entrepreneurship Development Programming (EDP) Cell is to encourage and facilitate the development of entrepreneurship as a viable career option and to empower individuals with the skills and knowledge required to start and manage successful businesses. The key objectives typically include:</p><p><strong>Entrepreneurship Promotion:</strong> To promote and create awareness about entrepreneurship as a career choice and economic development strategy.</p><p><strong>Skill Development:</strong> To equip individuals with the essential entrepreneurial skills, knowledge, and mindset required for starting and managing businesses.</p><p><strong>Business Incubation:</strong> To support the incubation of startup ventures by providing infrastructure, mentorship, and access to resources.</p><p><strong>Job Creation:</strong> To encourage and enable individuals to create job opportunities for themselves and others through entrepreneurial ventures.</p><p><strong>Innovation and Creativity:</strong> To foster innovation and creativity in business ideas and solutions.</p><p><strong>Economic Growth:</strong> To contribute to economic growth and development by cultivating a culture of entrepreneurship and fostering the growth of startups and small businesses.</p><p><strong>Function:</strong></p><p>The functions of an Entrepreneurship Development Programming (EDP) Cell involve a range of activities aimed at promoting entrepreneurship, providing guidance and resources to entrepreneurs, and facilitating the growth of startup ventures. These functions may include:</p><p><strong>Awareness Programs:</strong> Organizing seminars, workshops, and awareness campaigns to educate individuals about entrepreneurship and its benefits.</p><p><strong>Entrepreneurship Training:</strong> Offering training programs and courses that cover various aspects of entrepreneurship, including business planning, financial management, marketing, and innovation.</p><p><strong>Mentorship:</strong> Providing access to experienced mentors and advisors who can guide aspiring entrepreneurs in the development of their business ideas and strategies.</p><p><strong>Networking:</strong> Facilitating networking opportunities for entrepreneurs to connect with potential partners, investors, customers, and collaborators.</p><p><strong>Business Incubation:</strong> Offering physical or virtual spaces where startup ventures can work and access resources like office facilities, equipment, and funding opportunities.</p><p><strong>Access to Finance:</strong> Assisting entrepreneurs in identifying and securing funding sources, including grants, loans, and venture capital.</p><p><strong>Market Research:&nbsp;</strong>Supporting entrepreneurs in conducting market research to understand customer needs, trends, and market dynamics.</p><p><strong>Business Plan Development:</strong> Assisting entrepreneurs in creating comprehensive business plans, financial projections, and feasibility studies.</p><p><strong>Legal and Regulatory Guidance:</strong> Providing guidance on legal and regulatory requirements for starting and running a business.</p><p><strong>Innovation and Product Development:</strong> Encouraging innovation and helping entrepreneurs develop and refine their products or services.</p><p><strong>Startup Competitions:</strong> Organizing entrepreneurship competitions and pitching events to showcase and reward innovative business ideas.</p><p><strong>Monitoring and Evaluation:</strong> Assessing the progress and impact of entrepreneurship development programs and making improvements based on feedback and outcomes.</p><p><strong>Support for Scaling:</strong> Assisting successful startups in scaling up their operations and expanding their businesses.</p><p><strong>Committee members:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Entrepreneurship Development Programming (EDP) Cell</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>­­Dr. Chirag Vyas</strong></td><td><strong>Co-ordinator (Department of Physics)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Ankit Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Chemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Yati Vaidya</td><td>Member (Department of Microbiology)</td></tr><tr><td>Dr. Amit Mangrola</td><td>Member (Department of Biochemistry)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Jignesh Patel</td><td>Member (Department of Medical Technology)</td></tr><tr><td>Mr. Kailash Tiwari</td><td>Member (Department of Biotechnology)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','null','2023-12-06',NULL),(29,13,'Institutional Research Advisory Cell (IRAC)','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p>In order to review the research proposals, finalize the topic of research and review periodically and assist in the progress of the research work, the Institute has constituted research advisory committee (RAC).</p><p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p><ul><li>To review research activities of the Institute and develop broad objectives for research including research proposals to various funding bodies, MOU involved therein, as well as should evaluate the extent to which the research programme has met its objectives.</li><li>To assist with the development of faculty research programs within the departments&nbsp;</li><li>To advise to improve the existing infrastructural facilities both for academic and research.</li><li>To advice on thrust areas and disciplines for research activities for future development in research.</li><li>To integrate research outlook through regular curriculum implementation and curriculum enrichment activities among students and participants</li></ul><p><strong>Functions:</strong></p><ul><li>The Institute shall have a Research Advisory Committee mainly to frame guidelines pertaining to the conduct of PG &amp; Ph.D offered by it on the lines prescribed by the affiliating University and UGC</li><li>To create a conducive environment for promotion of Research &amp; Innovation activities in the institute.</li><li>Motivation of staff and students for conducting research.</li><li>To encourage students and faculty members to apply for short-term research grants and long-term research grants respectively.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>The mission of the Research Advisory Board (RAB) is to increase the quantity and quality of Academic Research, Sponsored Research, 