sp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;TOTAL AREA :-</strong></td><td>6442</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>','/images/infra/1d2fdf9f-c781-4163-8791.jpeg','2023-09-27','2023-09-27'),(169,13,'Internet','<p>Students can use the college\'s 30 Mbps internet connection, which is locally networked and connected to the main server through wi-fi. This connection is available for project work and seminar presentation preparation. Through the college\'s local area network, it has access to e-books, study resources, etc. Students can access the internet wirelessly in the classrooms thanks to these access points.</p>','/images/infra/6fbd17d0-b234-4a3c-92db.png','2023-09-27','2023-10-08'),(180,13,'Hostel facility','<p>Our college is pleased to offer exclusive hostel accommodations catering to both male and female students. Our hostels provide spacious, well-furnished rooms equipped with contemporary amenities to ensure the comfort and convenience of our residents. We maintain stringent hygiene standards in our kitchen facilities to guarantee the provision of nutritious meals. Moreover, our commitment to safety is reflected in the presence of a 24-hour security system across all of our campuses.</p><p>The institute takes pride in its exceptional hostel infrastructure, featuring spacious rooms and ample furniture. Recreation facilities are also provided, ensuring separate arrangements for both male and female residents. While residing in our hostels, student safety and security are paramount. Our diligent hostel wardens and vigilant security personnel work tirelessly to maintain a secure and comfortable living environment for all residents.</p>','/images/infra/2a99b200-1c15-4926-95c2.jpg','2023-10-08',NULL),(188,13,'Cafeteria and Bhojanalaya','<p>The college\'s canteen is situated within the campus premises and serves as a dining facility for various stakeholders, including day scholars, teaching staff, and non-teaching staff. We are dedicated to ensuring food safety and maintaining high-quality standards in the meals provided.&nbsp;</p><p>For our students who travel from distant locations, their day begins early in the morning. The canteen offers a range of meals throughout the day, including a nutritious morning breakfast, a wholesome mid-day meal, and a refreshing evening tea accompanied by delectable snacks.&nbsp;</p><p>Our primary goal is to uphold impeccable hygiene standards while delivering delicious and health-conscious food options.</p>','/images/infra/f770b593-0dd8-43e3-9217.jpeg','2023-10-09',NULL),(189,13,'Surveillance','<p>The whole college campus is fully equipped with a CCTV camera system. So it has to maintain and monitor more than a number of cameras every day. A better security performance, which is very helpful to watch the daily activities of the students, staff, workers, and public inside the campus regularly. If any students engage in inappropriate behaviour, it should be simple to spot them and take appropriate disciplinary action.</p>','/images/infra/b1ff827b-f9a5-4751-9325.jpeg','2023-10-09',NULL),(191,13,'ICT enabled rooms','<ul><li>SANPPGIS&amp;R has adequate classrooms for conducting lectures and tutorials for all students of all the Courses, provided with Air conditioner (AC), good ventilation, and wide corridors.</li><li>The rooms are built with adequate windows and well-furnished with facilities like White boards, fans, tube lights, ACs.</li><li>All classrooms are digital classrooms with Projectors and Screens for visual demonstrations.</li><li>All classrooms are equipped with high-speed Internet facilities and CCTV recordings.</li><li>&nbsp;All classrooms are fit with smooth flooring.</li><li>We have a well-ventilated air-conditioned seminar hall with a 300-seating capacity to conduct seminars, guest lectures and workshops furnished with all necessary facilities.</li></ul>','/images/infra/e0850b8e-f01f-47fd-86b9.jpeg','2023-10-09',NULL),(194,13,'Library Services and Facilities','<p><strong>LIBRARY SERVICES AND FACILITIES:</strong></p><ul><li>Internet Access: The library has 22 computers with internet access<strong>.</strong></li><li>Users of the Library\'s WEB OPAC (Online Public Access Catalogue) can look for information about individual books by author, title, subject, and the number of copies that are currently in stock.</li><li>Open Access for all students</li><li>Every year, a library orientation session is organized.</li><li>issue/return of books:</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Category of membership</td><td>No. of Books</td><td>Period of Loan</td></tr><tr><td>Students&nbsp;</td><td>2</td><td>6 days</td></tr><tr><td>Faculty Teaching</td><td>8</td><td>30 days</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Reading Hall:</strong>&nbsp;The Reading Hall consists of comfortable tables &amp; chairs with a seating capacity for 65 users.</li></ul><p>Books Available:&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Subject</strong></td><td><strong>No. of Titles</strong></td><td><strong>No. of Copies</strong></td><td><strong>No. of Titles/copies</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Chemistry:</strong></td><td>282</td><td>832</td><td>04</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Bio-Chemistry:</strong></td><td>95</td><td>213</td><td>01/(3c)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Information Technology:</strong></td><td>56</td><td>223</td><td>52</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mathematics:</strong></td><td>81</td><td>312</td><td>16/(31c)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Physics:</strong></td><td>128</td><td>352</td><td>23</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Micro-Biology:</strong></td><td>262</td><td>526</td><td>03</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Bio-Technology:</strong></td><td>115</td><td>281</td><td>26</td></tr><tr><td><strong>MLT:</strong></td><td>107</td><td>215</td><td>5/(19c)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>DMLT:</strong></td><td>19</td><td>51</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>1145</td><td>3005</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbod